1
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,760
Where are the bones in here?

2
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:18,040
I have no idea.

3
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,360
It was like this when I arrived.

4
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:19,960
This... this...

5
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:21,620
What exactly is going on here?

6
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:26,760
The natural phenomenon appeared again.

7
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:27,490
It seems that

8
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:29,520
the ancestor of the Song family

9
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:30,780
must be quite strange.

10
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:42,500
Please.

11
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:43,600
Please, after you.

12
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:44,800
Thank you all so much.

13
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:46,360
Next time,

14
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:47,960
I will host you all again.

15
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:49,440
Thank you so much.

16
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:50,240
Thank you all.

17
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:53,640
Thanks for your trouble.

18
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:56,200
Mayor, you're too polite.

19
00:00:57,440 --> 00:00:58,000
In the future,

20
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:58,930
this Taohua Town

21
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:00,290
will rely on you, Mayor.

22
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:02,480
I rely on all of you.

23
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:03,200
Thank you all.

24
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,599
Farewell.

25
00:01:04,599 --> 00:01:05,440
Take care.

26
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:06,680
Let's go.

27
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:24,400
You devil.

28
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:26,010
Take care, Miss Liu.

29
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:33,800
Auntie Huang.

30
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:38,080
Come here, quick.

31
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:08,610
You're drinking alone,

32
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,259
and didn't even invite me.

33
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:15,000
My dad seems to have changed.

34
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,530
He wasn't like this before.

35
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:18,720
Tell me,

36
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:20,720
how do you know your dad has changed?

37
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:21,760
Sometimes,

38
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:24,240
what people see isn't always the truth.

39
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,370
I saw it with my own eyes.

40
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,050
He was with some sketchy women,

41
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:32,680
and then he...

42
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,120
Stop.

43
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:36,780
Su Wanrong, you know what?

44
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:40,050
Sometimes, your eyes can deceive you.

45
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,460
You know your dad better than I do.

46
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,480
Listen to me.

47
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:47,040
Give yourself some time,

48
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:49,010
and give your dad some time too.

49
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:02,410
This wine

50
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:03,520
looks ordinary,

51
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,260
but it's quite strong.

52
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:12,880
Dad.

53
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,579
What are you doing?

54
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,130
What are you doing, Dad?

55
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:26,800
Wanrong.

56
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:29,970
How are you feeling?

57
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,200
Where is this?

58
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:34,520
My head...

59
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,880
The banknotes from the local gentry,

60
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:39,810
they aren't lost, are they?

61
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:42,760
At a time like this,

62
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:44,690
how can you still think about that?

63
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:47,000
I finally convinced

64
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,460
those prominent families

65
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,400
to fund

66
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,200
the repair of the stone tablet

67
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,530
to reassure the people.

68
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,159
It can also help the poor,

69
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,120
so people

70
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,800
will no longer be obsessed with superstition.

71
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,400
Nothing can go wrong.

72
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Liu Xian.

73
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,000
I really misunderstood you.

74
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,060
Huang Xian.

75
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:13,440
This...

76
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:15,400
The tablet of the Guardian Spirit.

77
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,600
The Guardian Spirit?

78
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,580
Where did it come from?

79
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:21,600
It was

80
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:24,640
those two women from yesterday.

81
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:25,920
Of them,

82
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:27,840
one is surnamed Liu,

83
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:30,440
and the other is surnamed Huang.

84
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:34,450
They claimed to be from a century-old prominent family in town.

85
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:35,800
They have a close relationship

86
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,040
with Song Ping.

87
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,040
They said

88
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,000
that Song Ping

89
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,540
is nowhere to be found now.

90
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:45,240
If I am willing to replace Song Ping

91
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:47,700
and continue to cooperate with them,

92
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,920
they will promise me benefits.

93
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:53,440
But

94
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,060
I remember Taohua Town

95
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:58,460
doesn't seem to have the prominent Liu and Huang families.

96
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,280
Could it be...

97
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,760
Could it be them?

98
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:04,860
In Taohua Town,

99
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,460
since its establishment,

100
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:09,400
there has been a legend of the Huang and Liu Immortals.

101
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,400
The Huang Immortal

102
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,600
refers to the weasel.

103
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:12,680
The Liu Immortal

104
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,810
refers to the snake.

105
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,840
For over 200 years,

106
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,800
residents here have often made offerings,

107
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,680
praying to them

108
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,200
to bless them with abundant harvests

109
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,320
and good weather.

110
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,520
The two families

111
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,400
received their own offerings,

112
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:28,000
and lived in peace.

113
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,420
Could it be that

114
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,330
the two women my father just mentioned

115
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,680
are these two immortals?

116
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,330
Grandpa.

117
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,050
Mr. Wang,

118
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,690
come out and take a look.

119
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:42,440
Where?

120
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:43,520
Mr. Wang,

121
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:44,280
look.

122
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,040
Go.

123
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,680
It will be either weasels or snakes by then.

124
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,200
Go.

125
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:54,600
Right.

126
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:55,640
If this continues,

127
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:56,400
this Taohua Town

128
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,120
will be unlivable.

129
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,440
Yes, exactly.

130
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:00,240
When I went to the outhouse this morning,

131
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,000
I was almost bitten by a snake on the butt.

132
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,000
I was so scared I couldn't even poop.

133
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,000
Even the mayor is possessed.

134
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,000
For us commoners to suffer,

135
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,400
it's only a matter of time.

136
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:09,800
Tell me about it.

137
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:10,400
Right.

138
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,620
I don't want to die.

139
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:13,120
This must be resolved today.

140
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,320
Everyone, quiet down

141
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,370
and listen to me.

142
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:17,720
With so many things happening in Taohua Town recently,

143
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,320
someone must be causing trouble behind the scenes,

144
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,320
trying to disrupt the normal order.

145
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,000
We must not let them succeed.

146
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,240
That's easy for you to say.

147
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,840
How are we commoners

148
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,600
supposed to fight the Song family ancestors

149
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,680
and the guardian spirits?

150
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:29,120
Yeah.

151
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:29,920
Exactly.

152
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,800
I think you're just trying to keep your position

153
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:32,860
by sacrificing us.

154
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:33,200
That's right.

155
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,000
What's the point of talking to her?

156
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:35,480
I think

157
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:38,130
we should just fend for ourselves.

158
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:40,480
Go.

159
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:40,960
Leave.

160
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:14,500
You can't completely blame them.

161
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,360
They are just ordinary people

162
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:19,260
who have always believed in ghosts and spirits.

163
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,840
With things like that happening,

164
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:24,760
how can they think like you?

165
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:25,520
Right?

166
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,200
The most terrifying thing

167
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,600
is not the lack of knowledge,

168
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,800
but that people would rather believe in ghosts and spirits

169
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,320
than believe in their own ability

170
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:34,380
to change all this.

171
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,960
I must change all this,

172
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:39,210
starting with Taohua Town.

173
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:45,120
By the way.

174
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:46,600
This time,

175
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,450
it might be the last time I help you.

176
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,360
The last time?

177
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,370
Are you leaving?

178
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:06,520
I...

179
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:08,180
What's wrong with him?

180
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:13,700
As the saying goes,

181
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,720
when immortals fight,

182
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:16,960
mortals suffer.

183
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:20,600
The reason the two immortals, Huang and Liu, are restless

184
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,440
is actually to fight for

185
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:25,220
the town hall's new protective immortal stone.

186
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,860
Even immortals fight each other.

187
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:31,000
Since ancient times, gods...

188
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,840
Whether they are immortals

189
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:32,560
or ghosts,

190
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,970
what they do is their business.

191
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,930
But as long as they dare to harm the people,

192
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,120
my Guitou Sword

193
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,400
will definitely settle the score with them.

194
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,200
Great. Well said.

195
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:43,860
In our town,

196
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:45,240
there is finally someone who can uphold justice.

197
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,280
Yes, exactly.

198
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,400
In the name of the Underworld Executioner, I warn you,

199
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:10,200
Immortals Huang and Liu, show yourselves at once.

200
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,640
If you continue to hide in the dark

201
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:14,800
and harm the people,

202
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:17,370
I will tear down this entire Town Hall,

203
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,600
uproot the land beneath my feet,

204
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:22,600
and completely destroy the spiritual energy here.

205
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,400
All your efforts will be in vain.

206
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,480
He actually dares to threaten the two guardian immortals.

207
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,880
He must have a death wish.

208
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,200
I just hope he doesn't drag us into this.

209
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,200
Go, go, go!

210
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,240
Hurry up!

211
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:37,680
Old pal,

212
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:43,000
it's time to get up and stretch your bones.
